~ Hello world, this is a test. this should be able to compile
~ feature-tour.wit — every AST kind in one file. Read top-to-bottom.
~ Goal is parser coverage, not clean rendering; some uses are intentionally
~ exotic so the AST tree exposes the structure.

reference ./feature-tour-missing.wit

~~ Block comment:
   this section shows prose, italic, and bold inline kinds.
   The inline citation pattern lives further down. ~~/

Plain prose with _italic_ and *bold* emphasis ~~ inline aside ~~/ in one line.

A second paragraph keeps the blank-line rule honest.

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Data definitions — single-line and block, scalar / record / collection.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

#one: 1 !!
#name: Robert !!
#meta: { a - 1, b - 2 } !!
#nums: [ 1, 2, 3 ] !!

~ Typed scalars — number / boolean / null inside record + collection
~ literals and the conditional RHS (v0.1.0 wires up these producers).
#flags: { count - 42, enabled - true, optional - null } !!
#values: [ 42, true, null ] !!

#person
  name: Robert
  age: 31
person#

#card
  title: My card
  body:
    Line one of the body.

    Line two after a paragraph break.
card#

#card_b
  title: My card
  body:
    Line one of the body.

    Line two after a paragraph break.
    @h1 heading test h1@
card_b#

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Node definitions — block, single-line, value-block, body-slot, additive.
~ Captures: explicit list and implicit derivation.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

#greeting ||name||
Hello, ::name::.
greeting#

~ Implicit captures — no ||...|| list, parser derives from interpolations.
#farewell
Goodbye, ::name::.
farewell#

~ Single-line def with captures + interpolation.
#cite: ::author:: (::year::) !!

~ Body-slot def (value-block shape).
#aside:
  An aside wraps ... and emits the wrapped body verbatim.
!!

~ Additive prefix — contributions accumulate under one name.
+#bibliography: @cite |author Smith| |year 2024| !!

+#bibliography:
  @cite
    author: "Came, H."
    year: 2024
  cite@
!!

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Node uses — every call shape against @cite (and friends).
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

A bare reference inline: @greeting.

@greeting
body content for greeting.
greeting@

~ Parens, space-separated — standalone self-closing.
@cite(author Smith, year 2024)

~ Parens, colon-separated — standalone self-closing.
@cite(author: Smith, year: 2024)

~ Pipes form on its own line — self-closing without `cite@`.
@cite |author Smith| |year 2024|

Record arg with hyphen @cite { author - Smith, year - 2024 } inline.

Record arg with colon @cite { author: Smith, year: 2024 } inline.

@cite
  author: Smith
  year: 2024
cite@

@cite author:Smith year:2024 cite@

Quoted-string record arg @cite { author: "Came, H.", year: 2024 } inline.

@cite author:@strong Smith strong@ year:2024 cite@

The variable name\:Tauraj is bad — backslash escape demo.

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Data access (dotted) — both bare and inside conditions.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

The first meta value is @meta.a and the person's name is @person.name.

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Conditionals — existence + comparison, then + else.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

(if @name) The name is set: @name. (end)

(if @person.age is 31) Thirty-one. (else) Not thirty-one. (end)

(if @flags.enabled is true) Enabled flag is on. (end)

(if @flags.optional is null) Optional value is unset. (end)

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Iteration.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

(each @nums as n) item @n; (end)

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Scripting — script block and inline script call.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

<%
function shout(s) {
  return String(s).toUpperCase();
}
%>

The system says: @scriptCall(shout, "hello")

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Multi-line param value via form-fill (M16).
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

@card
  title: Long card
  body:
    Multi
    line
    value
card@

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Block-aware capture substitution (M17).
~ Record values can carry block-level content (headings, lists, paragraphs).
~ Accessed downstream via @x.field, the captured value re-parses as full
~ document content and splices block-shaped pieces as blocks.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

The card_b title (inline use, single-paragraph value): @card_b.title.

The card_b body (block use, multi-paragraph plus embedded heading):

@card_b.body

~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------
~ Bibliography pattern — additive contributions get gathered at the use site.
~ ---------------------------------------------------------------------

@bibliography
